dc_description_s: This data represents boat access sites for Wisconsin in 2019.[This dataset is maintained by Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources. It is a compilation of public sites where boats can be legally launched into public waters in Wisconsin. It includes locations and data for both ramp and carry-in (canoe/kayak) launch sites throughout the state. These public launch sites are owned and maintained by State government (i.e. DNR, DOT, etc.) and local municipalities. No privately-owned sites are included in this database.This dataset is continually being updated and added to; this item displays the most current edits, however it may contain errors or omissions.]
uw_supplemental_s: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements.
